module.description: Resamples a MINC file along new spatial dimensions using a given transform

input.name: Transformation (use_input_sampling)
input.description: File giving world transformation using the input sampling without transforming. (Default = identity)

input.name: Transformation (tfm_input_sampling)
input.description: File giving world transformation with transforming the input sampling with the transform. (Default = identity)

input.name: Transformation (like)
input.description: File giving world transformation along with a model file for the resampling. (Default = identity)

input.name: Invert transformation
input.description: Invert the transformation before using it

input.name: No-Invert Transformation
input.description: Do not invert the transformation. This is the default setting.

input.name: Use Input Sampling
input.description: Use the input sampling without transforming (old behaviour).

input.name: Like
input.description: Specifies a model file for the resampling.

input.name: Spacetype
input.description: Set the spacetype attribute to a specified string.

input.name: Overwrite (clobber)
input.description: Overwrite existing file.

input.name: Don't Overwrite (no clobber)
input.description: Do not overwrite existing file. This is the default setting.

input.name: Verbose
input.description: Print out log messages as processing is being done. This is the default setting.

input.name: Quiet
input.description: Do not print out any log messages.

input.name: Talairach
input.description: Output is in Talairach space.

input.name: Units
input.description: Specify the units of the output sampling.

input.name: X-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the X dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Y-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the Y dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Z-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the Z dimension. (Default: 0)

input.description: Do not keep the real scale of the data. This is the default setting.

input.name: X-Step
input.description: Step size along the X dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Y-Step

input.name: Z-Start

input.description: Do nearest neighbour interpolation.

input.description: Write out byte data.

input.description: Write out short integer data.

dataModule.name: Manually Registered Rat Brain (Prior to Registration)

module.name: FLIRT (nii.gz)
module.description: FLIRT (FMRIB's Linear Image Registration Tool) is a fully automated robust and accurate tool for linear (affine) intra- and inter-modal brain image registration.

citations.citation:
S.M. Smith, M. Jenkinson, M.W. Woolrich, C.F. Beckmann, T.E.J. Behrens, H. Johansen-Berg, P.R. Bannister, M. De Luca, I. Drobnjak, D.E. Flitney, R. Niazy, J. Saunders, J. Vickers, Y. Zhang, N. De Stefano, J.M. Brady, and P.M. Matthews. Advances in functional and structural MR image analysis and implementation as FSL. NeuroImage, 23(S1):208-219, 2004
PMID: 15501092

input.name: Input
input.description: Specifies the input volume file path.

input.name: Reference
input.description: Specifies the input reference image.

output.name: Output
output.description: Specifies the output volume file path.

input.name: Initial Matrix File
input.description: Specifies the Input 4x4 affine matrix - autodetects format ascii/medx. Must specify <matrix-filename>.

output.name: Output Matrix File
output.description: Outputs the matrix in 4x4 ascii format. Must specify <matrix-filename>.

input.name: Datatype
input.description: Forces the output to one of the following data types: char, short, int, float, double.

input.name: Cost
input.description: Specifies the intensity based cost function. Options are: mutualinfo, corratio, normcorr, normmi, leastsq. (Default is corratio)

input.name: Search Cost
input.description: Specifies the type of search cost. Options are: mutualinfo, corratio, normcorr, normmi, leastsq. (Default is corratio)

input.name: Angle Rep
input.description: Specifies the type of angle rep. Options are: {quaternion,euler} (default is euler)

input.name: Interpolation
input.description: Specifies the type of final interpolation. Options are: trilinear, nearestneighbour, sinc. (Default is trilinear)

input.name: Sinc Width
input.description: Specifies the full sinc width in voxels. (Default is 7)

input.name: Bins
input.description: Specifies the number of histogram bins. (Default is 256)

input.name: Transform Degrees of Freedom
input.description:
Specifies the number of degrees of freedom. (Default is 12)
Note: Choose from 6,7,9 or 12 Degrees of Freedom (DOF) for full 3D registrations. Also includes a 3DOF 2D-to-2D registration mode which is selected using the -2D option. Note that it does not perform any search in 2D mode, and cannot deal with 2D to 3D registrations. More flexible DOF options are provided by the specific schedule files provided in $FSLDIR/etc/flirtsch.

input.name: No Sampling
input.description: Do not change input sampling.

input.name: Force Scaling
input.description: Forces rescaling even for low-res images.

input.name: Min Sampling
input.description: Sets minimum voxel dimension for sampling (in mm).

input.name: Apply XFM
input.description: Applies transform (no optimization). (Requires -init option)

input.name: Apply XFM with Isotropic Resample
input.description: As applyxfm but forces isotropic resampling. Must specify <scale>.

input.name: Padding Size
input.description: Interpolates outside image by size (in voxels). (Requires -applyxfm option)

input.name: Search X
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for x-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: Search Y
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for y-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: Search Z
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for z-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: No Search
input.description: Sets all angular search ranges to 0 0. (Sets 0 0 for -searchrx, -searchry and -searchrz)

input.name: Coarse Search
input.description: Specifies angular search range by specifying <delta_angle> (in degrees). (Default is 60)

input.name: Fine Search
input.description: Specifies angular search range by specifying <delta_angle> (in degrees). (Default is 18)

input.name: Schedule
input.description:
Schedule file specifies what transformations/DOF are allowed and how the optimisation is performed. Must specify <schedule-file>. (Replaces default schedule)
Note: Several other schedule files could be used - including 3D translation only schedules, etc. These are all stored in ${FSLDIR}/etc/flirtsch.

input.name: Reference Weight
input.description: Use weights for reference volume. Must specify input <volume> for weights.

input.name: Input Weight
input.description: Use weights for input volume. Must specify input <volume> for weights.

input.name: 2D
input.description: Use 2D rigid body mode. (Ignores -dof option)

input.name: Verbose
input.description: Specifies level of verboseness. (0 is least and default)

input.name: Pause
input.description: Enables pause at each stage of transformation.

input.name: Sinc Window
input.description: Specifies the type of sinc window. Options are: rectangular, hanning, blackman.

input.name: Version
input.description: Prints the version information and exit

input.name: Help
input.description: Prints help information and exit.

module.name: Analyze Image to MNC
module.description: This program converts Analyze Image to Minc file format.

input.name: Model Minc File
input.description: Model volume for the Analyze file being converted (i.e. create file using world coordinates from this file).

input.name: Overwrite
input.description: Clobber (overwrite) existing output if it already exists.

input.name: Input Analyze Image File
input.description: Specifies the input Analyze Volume file path to be converted.

output.name: Output Minc
output.description: Specifies the output MNC file path.

input.name: Verbose
input.description: Instructs the program to be verbose.

input.name: No Verbose
input.description: Opposite of -verbose. (Default)

input.name: Input Minc
input.description: Specifies the input MNC Label file path.

input.name: Parameters
input.description:
mincreshape -help Command-specific options: General options: -clobber: Overwrite existing file. -noclobber: Do not overwrite existing file (default). -verbose: Print out log messages as processing is being done (default).
-quiet: Do not print out any log messages. -max_chunk_size_in_kb: Specify the maximum size of the copy buffer (in kbytes). Default value: 4096 Image conversion options (pixel type and range): -filetype: Don't do any type conversion (default). -byte: Convert to byte data -short: Convert to short integer data -int: Convert to 32-bit integer data -long: Superseded by -int -float: Convert to single-precision floating-point data -double: Convert to double-precision floating-point data -signed: Convert to signed integer data -unsigned: Convert to unsigned integer data -valid_range: Valid range for output data (pixel values) Default value: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 -image_range: Normalize images to a given minimum and maximum Default value: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 -normalize: Normalize images to file minimum and maximum. -nonormalize: Do not normalize images (default). -nopixfill: Do not convert out-of-range values in input file. -pixfill: Replace out-of-range values in input file by smallest value (default). -pixfillvalue: Specify new value to replace out-of-range values in input file. Default value: -1.79769e+308 Image conversion options (dimension direction and size): -scalar: Convert vector images to scalar images. -noscalar: Do not convert vector images to scalar images (default). +direction: Flip images to give positive step value for spatial axes. -direction: Flip images to give negative step value for spatial axes. -anydirection: Don't flip images along spatial axes (default). +xdirection: Flip images to give positive xspace:step value (left-to-right). -xdirection: Flip images to give negative xspace:step value (right-to-left). -xanydirection: Don't flip images along x-axis. +ydirection: Flip images to give positive yspace:step value (post-to-ant). -ydirection: Flip images to give negative yspace:step value (ant-to-post). -yanydirection: Don't flip images along y-axis. +zdirection: Flip images to give positive zspace:step value (inf-to-sup). -zdirection: Flip images to give negative zspace:step value (sup-to-inf). -zanydirection: Don't flip images along z-axis. -keepaspect: Preserve aspect ratio when resizing images. -nokeepaspect: Do not preserve aspect ratio when resizing images (default). -imgsize: Specify the desired image size. Default value: -1 -rowsize: Specify the desired number of rows in the image. Default value: -1 -colsize: Specify the desired number of columns in the image. Default value: -1 -dimsize: Specify the size of a named dimension (<dimension>=<size>). Reshaping options: -transverse: Write out transverse slices -sagittal: Write out sagittal slices -coronal: Write out coronal slices -dimorder: Specify dimension order (<dim1>,<dim2>,<dim3>,...). -dimrange: Specify range of dimension subscripts (<dim>=<start>[,<count>]). -start: Specifies corner of hyperslab (C conventions for indices) -count: Specifies edge lengths of hyperslab to read Missing data options: -nofill: Use value zero for points outside of input volume (default) -fill: Use a fill value for points outside of input volume -fillvalue: Specify a fill value for points outside of input volume Default value: 1.79769e+308 Generic options for all commands: -help: Print summary of command-line options and abort -version: Print version number of program and exit

module.name: MINC Resample
module.description: Resamples a MINC file along new spatial dimensions using a given transform

input.name: Transformation (use_input_sampling)
input.description: File giving world transformation using the input sampling without transforming. (Default = identity)

input.name: Transformation (tfm_input_sampling)
input.description: File giving world transformation with transforming the input sampling with the transform. (Default = identity)

input.name: Transformation (like)
input.description: File giving world transformation along with a model file for the resampling. (Default = identity)

input.name: Invert transformation
input.description: Invert the transformation before using it

input.name: No-Invert Transformation
input.description: Do not invert the transformation. This is the default setting.

input.name: Use Input Sampling
input.description: Use the input sampling without transforming (old behaviour).

input.name: Like
input.description: Specifies a model file for the resampling.

input.name: Spacetype
input.description: Set the spacetype attribute to a specified string.

input.name: Overwrite (clobber)
input.description: Overwrite existing file.

input.name: Don't Overwrite (no clobber)
input.description: Do not overwrite existing file. This is the default setting.

input.name: Verbose
input.description: Print out log messages as processing is being done. This is the default setting.

input.name: Quiet
input.description: Do not print out any log messages.

input.name: Talairach
input.description: Output is in Talairach space.

input.name: Units
input.description: Specify the units of the output sampling.

input.name: X-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the X dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Y-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the Y dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Z-Elements
input.description: Number of elements along the Z dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: TFM Input Sampling
input.description: Transform the input sampling with the transform. This is the default setting.

input.name: Do Not Keep Real Range
input.description: Do not keep the real scale of the data. This is the default setting.

input.name: X-Step
input.description: Step size along the X dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Y-Step
input.description: Step size along the Y dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: Z-Step
input.description: Step size along the Z dimension. (Default: 0)

input.name: X-Start
input.description: Start point along the X dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Y-Start
input.description: Start point along the Y dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Z-Start
input.description: Start point along the Z dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308)

input.name: X-DirCos
input.description: Direction cosines along the X dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Y-DirCos
input.description: Direction cosines along the Y dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Z-DirCos
input.description: Direction cosines along the Z dimension. (Default: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Transverse
input.description: Write out transverse slices.

input.name: Sagittal
input.description: Write out sagittal slices.

input.name: Coronal
input.description: Write out coronal slices.

input.name: Direction Cosines
input.description: Direction cosines along each dimension (X, Y, Z).

input.name: Nearest Neighbor
input.description: Do nearest neighbour interpolation.

input.name: Byte
input.description: Write out byte data.

input.name: Short
input.description: Write out short integer data.

input.name: Integer
input.description: Write out 32-bit integer data.

input.name: Origin
input.description: Origin of first pixel in 3D space. (Default: 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Long
input.description: Write out long integer data.

input.name: Float
input.description: Write out single-precision floating-point data.

input.name: Double
input.description: Write out double-precision floating-point data.

input.name: Keep Real Range
input.description: Keep the real scale of the input volume.

input.name: Signed
input.description: Write signed integer data.

input.name: Trilinear
input.description: Do trilinear interpolation.

input.name: Unsigned
input.description: Write unsigned integer data.

input.name: Tricubic
input.description: Do tricubic interpolation.

input.name: Range
input.description: Valid range for output data (Default: -1.79769e+308 -1.79769e+308)

input.name: Fill Value
input.description: Specify a fill value for points outside of input volume. (Default: 1.79769e+308)

input.name: Fill
input.description: Use a fill value for points outside of input volume.

input.name: No Fill
input.description: Use value zero for points outside of input volume

input.name: Input
input.description: Specify the input file path.

input.name: Standard Sampling
input.description: Set the sampling to standard values (step, start and dircos).

input.name: Step
input.description: Step size along each dimension (X, Y, Z). (Default: 0 0 0)

input.name: No Keep Real Range
input.description: Do not keep the real scale of the data. This is the default setting.

input.name: Number of Elements
input.description: Number of elements along each dimension (X, Y, Z) .

input.name: Start
input.description: Start point along each dimension (X, Y, Z).

module.name: FLIRT (nii.gz)
module.description: FLIRT (FMRIB's Linear Image Registration Tool) is a fully automated robust and accurate tool for linear (affine) intra- and inter-modal brain image registration.

citations.citation:
S.M. Smith, M. Jenkinson, M.W. Woolrich, C.F. Beckmann, T.E.J. Behrens, H. Johansen-Berg, P.R. Bannister, M. De Luca, I. Drobnjak, D.E. Flitney, R. Niazy, J. Saunders, J. Vickers, Y. Zhang, N. De Stefano, J.M. Brady, and P.M. Matthews. Advances in functional and structural MR image analysis and implementation as FSL. NeuroImage, 23(S1):208-219, 2004
PMID: 15501092

input.name: Input
input.description: Specifies the input volume file path.

input.name: Reference
input.description: Specifies the input reference image.

output.name: Output
output.description: Specifies the output volume file path.

input.name: Initial Matrix File
input.description: Specifies the Input 4x4 affine matrix - autodetects format ascii/medx. Must specify <matrix-filename>.

output.name: Output Matrix File
output.description: Outputs the matrix in 4x4 ascii format. Must specify <matrix-filename>.

input.name: Datatype
input.description: Forces the output to one of the following data types: char, short, int, float, double.

input.name: Cost
input.description: Specifies the intensity based cost function. Options are: mutualinfo, corratio, normcorr, normmi, leastsq. (Default is corratio)

input.name: Search Cost
input.description: Specifies the type of search cost. Options are: mutualinfo, corratio, normcorr, normmi, leastsq. (Default is corratio)

input.name: Angle Rep
input.description: Specifies the type of angle rep. Options are: {quaternion,euler} (default is euler)

input.name: Interpolation
input.description: Specifies the type of final interpolation. Options are: trilinear, nearestneighbour, sinc. (Default is trilinear)

input.name: Sinc Width
input.description: Specifies the full sinc width in voxels. (Default is 7)

input.name: Bins
input.description: Specifies the number of histogram bins. (Default is 256)

input.name: Transform Degrees of Freedom
input.description:
Specifies the number of degrees of freedom. (Default is 12)
Note: Choose from 6,7,9 or 12 Degrees of Freedom (DOF) for full 3D registrations. Also includes a 3DOF 2D-to-2D registration mode which is selected using the -2D option. Note that it does not perform any search in 2D mode, and cannot deal with 2D to 3D registrations. More flexible DOF options are provided by the specific schedule files provided in $FSLDIR/etc/flirtsch.

input.name: No Sampling
input.description: Do not change input sampling.

input.name: Force Scaling
input.description: Forces rescaling even for low-res images.

input.name: Min Sampling
input.description: Sets minimum voxel dimension for sampling (in mm).

input.name: Apply XFM
input.description: Applies transform (no optimization). (Requires -init option)

input.name: Apply XFM with Isotropic Resample
input.description: As applyxfm but forces isotropic resampling. Must specify <scale>.

input.name: Padding Size
input.description: Interpolates outside image by size (in voxels). (Requires -applyxfm option)

input.name: Search X
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for x-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: Search Y
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for y-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: Search Z
input.description: Specifies <min_angle> & <max_angle> for z-dimension angular search range (in degrees). (Default is -90 90)

input.name: No Search
input.description: Sets all angular search ranges to 0 0. (Sets 0 0 for -searchrx, -searchry and -searchrz)

input.name: Coarse Search
input.description: Specifies angular search range by specifying <delta_angle> (in degrees). (Default is 60)

input.name: Fine Search
input.description: Specifies angular search range by specifying <delta_angle> (in degrees). (Default is 18)

input.name: Schedule
input.description:
Schedule file specifies what transformations/DOF are allowed and how the optimisation is performed. Must specify <schedule-file>. (Replaces default schedule)
Note: Several other schedule files could be used - including 3D translation only schedules, etc. These are all stored in ${FSLDIR}/etc/flirtsch.

input.name: Reference Weight
input.description: Use weights for reference volume. Must specify input <volume> for weights.

input.name: Input Weight
input.description: Use weights for input volume. Must specify input <volume> for weights.

input.name: 2D
input.description: Use 2D rigid body mode. (Ignores -dof option)

input.name: Verbose
input.description: Specifies level of verboseness. (0 is least and default)

input.name: Pause
input.description: Enables pause at each stage of transformation.

input.name: Sinc Window
input.description: Specifies the type of sinc window. Options are: rectangular, hanning, blackman.

input.name: Version
input.description: Prints the version information and exit

input.name: Help
input.description: Prints help information and exit.

module.name: Volume Two Independent Wilcoxon Test
module.description:
This module computes the Two-independent samples Wilcoxon test on volumetric data.
Responses are the VOLUME/IMAGE intensities at each voxel location.

input.name: Design Matrix
input.description:
Enter Design Matrix. See the template here:
http://wiki.stat.ucla.edu/socr/index.php/SOCR_EduMaterials_AnalysesCommandLineVolume2Samples_T_test

input.name: Regressors Specification
input.description:
Regressor Specifications.
One Regressor must be specified from the list of predictors/columns/covariates listed in the Design Matrix (see first argument). You must specify 2 values for this predictor that will be used to extract the image files that represent the 2 groups (no spaces!)
Example: -regressors GROUP=1,2

input.name: Header Flag
input.description:
Header Flag (-h).
Required for all Design Matrices.

input.name: Volume Dimensions
input.description:
Specify the Z Volume Dimension Order is: (Z, Y, X):
Example: -dim 220 220 220
For 1D or 2D data, use 1 for the higher demensions.

input.name: Data Type
input.description:
Specify the Input Data type:
Example: -data_type 2 -data_type [1,2,3,4]: Type=1 is for Byte, Type=2 is for Unsigned Short integer, Type=3 is for Signed Short Integer, and Type=4 is for 4Byte=Float Volume Input;

input.name: Mask File
input.description:
Enter an optional Mask File. It is used to restrict the voxel-based domain of the Regression Analysis.
If no Mask is specified all voxes are processed independently.
Example: -mask /ifs/adni/3T/PERMS/IVO/JACOBIANS/3T_bl_002_S_0413.img

input.name: Byte-Order
input.description:
-byteorder string: string is one of {big, little, other}.
* big = BIG_ENDIAN processor * little = LITTLE_ENDIAN processor * other = default processor (java.nio.ByteOrder.nativeOrder())

output.name: P-value Output Volume
output.description:
This should be the same value as the Output P-value parameter.
This is a pipeline workaround!

output.name: T-statistic Output Volume
output.description:
This is a second reference to the same T-statistics output file.
This is a Pipeline workaround
